  "text": "The diversification benefits of real estate, and its role in institutional investment portfolios is well documented in the literature. [CITATION_1] summarize the literature on real estate asset allocation and report a wide range of recommended allocations. These vary from 0% to 67% and depend on the structure of the data and time period analyzed. HudsonWilson et al. [2005] emphasize real estate's low correlation with stocks and bonds, high riskadjusted returns, reliable cash flows and hedging characteristics against unexpected inflation.",
